        <h1 class="section-heading">üñ®Ô∏è Introduction to Python</h1>
        <div class="intro-text">
            <p>When you learn a new language, the first thing you usually do is say ‚ÄúHello‚Äù. In the same way, when we learn a programming language like Python, the first thing we do is make the computer say something.</p>
            <p>This is done using the <strong>print</strong> command.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">ü§î Why Do We Print in Python?</h2>
            <p>Printing means showing something on the screen.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Just like when you write a note on paper for someone to read ‚úçÔ∏è,</li>
                <li>Printing in Python shows messages, numbers, or results on your computer screen.</li>
                <li>It‚Äôs the easiest way to talk to the computer and check if your program is working.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">üíª How to Print in Python</h2>
            <p>The command is very simple:</p>
            <pre><code>print("Hello, ghost World!")</code></pre>
            <p>When you run this program, your computer will show:</p>
            <pre><code>Hello, ghost World!</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">üìå Examples of Printing</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Printing a message</strong>
                    <pre><code>print("Welcome to Python learning!")</code></pre>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Printing numbers</strong>
                    <pre><code>print(10)
print(25 + 30) # It will also calculate</code></pre>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Printing multiple things together</strong>
                    <pre><code>print("My name is ghost, I am", 20, "years old")</code></pre>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">üåç Real-Life Situations Where Printing is Useful</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Banking apps:</strong> Showing ‚ÄúTransaction Successful‚Äù after you transfer money.</li>
                <li><strong>Games:</strong> Showing ‚ÄúGame Over‚Äù or your score.</li>
                <li><strong>Shopping websites:</strong> Showing the price of items in your cart.</li>
                <li><strong>Tickets/Invoices:</strong> Printing booking confirmations or bills.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>In short, printing is how a computer shares information back to us.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
